Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Cerro Verde, Edegel, Telefonica

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-03-31T21:14:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/peru-stocks-buenaventura-cerro-verde-edegel-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Peru trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index gained 0.7 percent to 21,957.49. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 1.1 percent to 2,940.70.  Utilities and construction shares gained after investor
concerns eased over the outcome of the April 10 elections, said
Ernesto Ferrand, a trader at Lima-based brokerage Andes
Securities SAB.  Telefonica del Peru SAA (TEF PE), the local unit of
 Telefonica SA (TEF) , rebounded 4.3 percent to $25.03. Edegel SA
(EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian unit of  Spain ’s Endesa SA, rose 2.9
percent to 1.80 soles.  Cementos Pacasmayo SAA (CPACASI1)  (CPACASC1 PE), the
Hochschild Group’s cement producer, gained 2.7 percent to 6.88
soles.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of
Gerdau SA, Latin America’s largest steelmaker, rose 2.4 percent
to 1.68 soles.  Miners gained after metals advanced in New York and  London .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, rose 2.9 percent to $43.30. Cia.
Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based silver and zinc
producer, gained for a third day, adding 2.4 percent to 1.30
soles. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., rose 2.3 percent to $45.30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at   aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  